This paper deals with analyzing and measuring the quality of gadgets used in low-level exploits, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also involves analyzing binaries produced when compiling programs, which could fall under software engineering (cs.SE) and programming languages (cs.PL). Additionally, the paper discusses the implementation of Intel's MPX CPU extensions, which could fall under computer architecture (cs.AR) and systems and control (cs.SY).
